column16: While this is called an "implementation guide", there doesn't seem to be enough information telling the reader how a healthcare directory is evisioned to work using FHIR nor how to implement one (i.e, the expected interactions). Use cases are mentioned but not included, and expected behaviors are not adequately described (e.g., default server capability statements, no search parameters, sparse conformace requirements). This seems to be more a collection of profiles rather than an IG in the classic sense - perhaps this is partially how FHIR publishes IGs, or perhaps a result of this particular project's lifecycle.  But for now, too much is left to the imagination of the reader.  In addition there are numerous TBDs and "Specific <feature>  are under analysis." statements. Because this is STU1, I will not vote negative, but this isn't yet ready for prime time.
column17: Insufficient detail in Guide

column16: This IG creates duplicate profiles for practitioner, organization etc. where existing US Core profiles already exist. This IG should either a) derive from those profiles, adding additional constraints and extensions as  necessary and compromising on "nice to have" items that would otherwise be conflicts, or b) clearly describe the departure from US Core on the Home tab of the IG and justify why the departure was absolutely necessary. Note: There is currently no mention of US core on the home tab. It is as if this IG was developed without considering existing work.
column17: Consider how this IG relates to the US Core IG
